The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 St Pauls will meet South Point in the boys final of the Inter-school Tennis meet, organised by Indian Tennis Academy at SAI. In the semi-finals on Monday, St Pauls beat La Martiniere 2-1, while South Point overcame Calcutta Boys by a similar margin. St Pauls were represented by Avijit and Arijit Mullick while Rohan Roy and Arcopravo Rakshit played for South Point.

 In girls section, Mahadevi Birla reached the final defeating defending champions Calcutta International 2-0. The other semi-final between La Martiniere and Modern High was tied 1-1 at the close. The deciding doubles match will be played on Wednesday before the finals. Tuesday being the rest day, all the finals will be played on Wednesday.

 CRICKET: U-15 Polly Umrigar Trophy Bengal vs Jharkhand (Eastern Railway Sports Complex, 8.45 am) n East Zone Inter-university meet matches at various grounds.




